Defendant Terrance M Reimer in court with attorney Peter M Wolff.  Pablo Galaviz appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Defendant enters a plea of guilty to counts 1 and 2. Court conducted plea colloquy with defendant. Court finds defendant guilty of counts 1 and 2. 

The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

Count 1
IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE of: 

90 DAYS JAIL WITH HUBER 

Term of Probation: 1 YEAR CONSECUTIVE TO ANY OTHER SENTENCE

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:  
*AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
*Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s ; 
*No Use or Possession of alcohol, controlled substances or drug paraphernalia.
*No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
*Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are prescribed.
*Inform Agent of all prescriptions
*Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
*Maintain employment and/or combination of schooling 

Condition Time: 45 DAYS NON WORKING HOURS WITH STANDARD RELEASE CONDITIONS  STAYED - To be used at agent's discretion. 

COURT COSTS:  $243.00 to be paid as a condition of probation;


COUNT 2

HUBER:  45 days, w/Standard Release Conditions. Defendant to report to Huber facility FORTHWITH - 7 days credit given. 

FINE: $1494.00 Apply $1000.00 cash bail, balance to be paid as a condition of probation;

BLOOD DRAW FEE:  $35.00 paid through Waukesha County Circuit Court to be forward to Waukesha Police Department or to be converted to a civil judgment for non payment of fee.

D/L REVOCATION: 24 months;

IGNITION INTERLOCK: 24 months;

Attendance at a Victim Impact Panel on:  November 18, 2015. Defendant to serve 30 days huber, consecutive, as penalty for failure to attend Victim Impact Panel.

Other:  AODA ASSESSMENT AND FOLLOW THROUGH.
